"/> Are you VAT registered??

If not, then you can't claim the VAT, but you may be able to claim the
import tax, duty or VAT as a personal import. Easier if it's another EU
member.

Best to contact your local VAT office and/or HM Custom &amp; Excise.

Antiques and/or &quot;works of arts&quot; have their own schedule under the VAT
scheme, usually a Zero rate will applies. ie: antique=100years, work of
art, if under a 100years old, should be signed or attributable, this
sometimes is sticky point and you may have to argue the point with
Customs.

The VAT office has an appropriate help leaflet explaining the full
schedule and scope. HM Custom &amp; Excise have similar explaining personal
importation.

They will not be vague. It really depends if you're a business of a
private.

